# Git Push Failure Log

## Metadata

- Timestamp: 20260708-052525
- Branch: main
- Local Commit: `1976e1c`
- Target Remote: `origin`
- Final Status: blocked by missing HTTPS helper and denied SSH execution in the current environment

## Error Output

```text
git push origin main
git: 'remote-https' is not a git command. See 'git --help'.

git remote set-url --push origin git@github.com:decline-llc/netsentry.git
git push origin main
fatal: cannot exec 'ssh': Permission denied
fatal: unable to fork
```

## Root Cause Analysis

- The current Git installation does not provide the `git-remote-https` helper, so HTTPS push to the approved GitHub remote cannot start.
- The environment exposes `/usr/bin/ssh`, but direct execution returns `Permission denied`, so SSH push cannot start either.
- Because both transport paths fail before authentication, the local commits remain unpushed even though the repository content is committed.

## Remaining Risk

- Commit `1976e1c` exists only locally until a host with working Git transport helpers pushes it.
- The release workflow itself has not been exercised on a real version tag.
- Full `make`/`go` quality gates are still pending in a provisioned environment.

## Next Action

- Retry `git push origin main` from an environment with either working `git-remote-https` support or executable `ssh`.
